 Synix was praised as the new must-have TV set that is focused on providing consumers with the "home cinema experience" during a launch at the Ole Sereni on April 7 attended by local celebrities MCA Tricky and Pascal Tokodi, among others. “Syinix is committed to being a top international brand and the best companion for African families,” Syinix Global CMO Bin Xing said. The android TV is a visual feast, according to MCA tricky, who swears by the TV's game-changing features, which include an in-built satellite, 4K resolution, and 2*12 stereo audio. “I recommend Syinix HDR U51 Android TV as it allows me to enjoy a visual feast as it looks absolutely  vivid and sounds clear, I know it is because that it is 4K resolution and 2*12 stereo audio.  Syinix U51 android TV meets all my imagination for a best TV I can get.“ the comedian said. According to Martin, the head of Android Platform Partnerships, users will be able to surf through the endless sea of 400,000+ movies and shows from across streaming services thanks to the TV's Google 11 OS and voice remote control. Users will also be able to cast photos, videos, and music from their smart devices to their TVs, thanks to Chromecast's built-in functionality. The launch also revealed a full range of Syinix Android TVs, including the 2K Android TV A51 Series, the younger Syinix U51 Series, and the flagship WLED Android TV Q51 Series, giving consumers more options. In addition, Syinix is also an expert in large home appliances such as refrigerators and washing machines, and fully automatic kitchen appliances. Syinix, the fastest growing home appliance brand in Africa, can be compared to other home appliance brands such as LG, Samsung and Sony. 